						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Tribhuvanachchakravartti Kulōttuṅga (II) Year 2: 1135 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record that the priests of the temple received <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> from Sekkiḻān Bālavaṟāvāyaṇ of Kuṉṟattūr in Kuṉṟattūr-Nāḍu (a sub-division) of Kulōttuṅgachōḷa-vaḷanāḍu for burning a perpetual lamp to the god for the merit of Kaḷappāyanāṟ and they agreed to burn the same. </p>						

